  "market_context": "Following a V-shape reversal and consolidation forming a range with an inside bar, Monday and Tuesday remain internal to the range. Wednesday sweeps the range low and prints a candle-2 closure, but the closure is itself a bearish expansion candle, making it suboptimal and requiring lower time frame confirmation.",
  "key_observation": "Because Wednesday's candle-2 closure was not ideal (bearish expansion body), the analyst required an hourly change in state of delivery — price opening, forming a low, and closing above the swing high of the down-close series — to validate both daily and weekly bullish profiles.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify a V-shape reversal followed by consolidation with an inside bar, defining a tradable range.",
    "Step 2: Observe Monday and Tuesday remain internal to the range, deferring directional action to Wednesday.",
    "Step 3: Note Wednesday sweeps the range low and prints a candle-2 closure, but flag it as suboptimal because the closure itself is a bearish expansion candle.",
    "Step 4: Drop to the hourly chart to seek a change in state of delivery — confirm whether price closes above the series of down-close candles that formed the low.",
    "Step 5: Anticipate a bullish intraday OHLC sequence (Open-Low-High-Close) to confirm both daily and weekly profile.",
    "Step 6: Once the hourly closes over the CISD level, target the failure swings above the range.",
    "Step 7: Observe Thursday delivers expansion (continuation off the Wednesday reversal) and Friday continues higher off a protected swing."
  ],
  "outcome": "Hourly CISD confirmed, Thursday delivered the expansion continuation, and Friday added another expansion off a protected swing — successful bullish continuation from the range low sweep.",
  "lessons": "When a candle-2 closure forms with a suboptimal body (bearish expansion in a bullish setup), do not commit on the daily alone — require an hourly CISD with the proper intraday OHLC sequence before trading toward the failure swings above.",
